        "---\n",
        "## ⌬ 2. Example: Tidal Evolution of a Multi-Moon System\n",
        "\n",
        "In this example, we will simulate a central host (like a gas giant) and two moons near a 2:1 mean-motion resonance. We will use `REBOUNDx` to apply a simple tidal force (constant time lag) to the central body to demonstrate how energy dissipation affects the inner moon's orbit over time. Finally, we will extract and plot the semi-major axis and eccentricity evolution.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "example_md"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# 1. Initialize Simulation\n",
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "sim = rebound.Simulation()\n",
        "sim.units = ('yr', 'AU', 'Msun')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add a central host (e.g., a Jupiter-mass planet)\n",
        "sim.add(m=1e-3, r=0.0005, hash=\"Host\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add an inner moon and an outer moon near a 2:1 resonance\n",
        "sim.add(m=1e-7, r=1e-5, a=0.01, e=0.05, hash=\"Moon1\")\n",
        "sim.add(m=1e-7, r=1e-5, a=0.01587, e=0.01, hash=\"Moon2\")\n",
        "\n",
        "sim.move_to_com() # Move to center of momentum frame\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# 2. Add REBOUNDx Tidal Forces\n",
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "rebx = reboundx.Extras(sim)\n",
        "tides = rebx.load_force(\"tides_constant_time_lag\")\n",
        "rebx.add_force(tides)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set the tidal parameters for the Host body\n",
        "# (Using exaggerated values here just so the effect is visible quickly in a short sim)\n",
        "sim.particles[\"Host\"].params[\"tctl_k2\"] = 0.3\n",
        "sim.particles[\"Host\"].params[\"tctl_tau\"] = 1e-2 \n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# 3. Integration & Data Collection\n",
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "N_outputs = 500\n",
        "times = np.linspace(0, 100, N_outputs)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Arrays to store orbital elements\n",
        "a1, e1 = np.zeros(N_outputs), np.zeros(N_outputs)\n",
        "a2, e2 = np.zeros(N_outputs), np.zeros(N_outputs)\n",
        "\n",
        "for i, t in enumerate(times):\n",
        "    sim.integrate(t)\n",
        "    a1[i] = sim.particles[\"Moon1\"].a\n",
        "    e1[i] = sim.particles[\"Moon1\"].e\n",
        "    a2[i] = sim.particles[\"Moon2\"].a\n",
        "    e2[i] = sim.particles[\"Moon2\"].e\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# 4. Plotting the Orbital Evolution\n",
        "# ---------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 8), sharex=True)\n",
        "plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Semi-major axis plot\n",
        "ax1.plot(times, a1, label=\"Moon 1\", color='b')\n",
        "ax1.plot(times, a2, label=\"Moon 2\", color='r')\n",
        "ax1.set_ylabel(\"Semi-major Axis (AU)\", fontsize=12)\n",
        "ax1.set_title(\"Orbital Evolution Under Tidal Dissipation\", fontsize=14)\n",
        "ax1.legend(loc=\"upper right\")\n",
        "ax1.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Eccentricity plot\n",
        "ax2.plot(times, e1, label=\"Moon 1 (e)\", color='b')\n",
        "ax2.plot(times, e2, label=\"Moon 2 (e)\", color='r')\n",
        "ax2.set_ylabel(\"Eccentricity\", fontsize=12)\n",
        "ax2.set_xlabel(\"Time (Years)\", fontsize=12)\n",
        "ax2.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
