        "### 📊 Understanding the Output\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Semi-Major Axis (a):** You will notice the inner moon's semi-major axis slowly decaying due to the exaggerated tidal forces applied via `REBOUNDx`. The outer moon remains relatively stable.\n",
        "* **Eccentricity (e):** The eccentricities exhibit periodic oscillations. When moons are near or captured into a Mean-Motion Resonance (MMR), these oscillations become highly coupled.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Note on Performance:** When running large-scale tidal evolution over millions of orbits, Python's `multiprocessing` library is recommended to batch multiple initial conditions across different CPU cores.\n"
